history.content:
CS61C does have recording. However you are required to attend lab check-offs for 15min every week. There are plenty of check-offs slots you can pick even for international students.

----

As for 16B..in the Spring we have a lot more students than in the Fall, so we have lab slots 8AM PST to 8PM PST Monday to Friday, except during lecture times, so I guess you should be accommodated. The nature of labs isn't clear yet, but both Fall and Summer had remote labs with each student being shipped the kit and having to build their own hardware. There is no clarity on how the labs will be for the Spring.
CS61C does have recording. However you are required to attend lab check-offs for 15min every week. There are plenty of check-offs slots you can pick even for international students.

Because many courses for next semester will also be remote instructions and I'm not in Berkeley time zone, I wonder whether there will be a list about which cs class doesn't require attendance and so I can watch recording? What about cs61c, ee16b? Where can I find these kind of information? Thanks!
history.subject: recording of cs class in spring semester
